  "prompt": "What is potassium sorbate?",
  "response": "Potassium sorbate is a widely used food preservative that helps prevent the growth of molds and yeasts in various food and beverage products. It is the potassium salt of sorbic acid, a naturally occurring compound found in some berries. Potassium sorbate is commonly used in:\n\n1. Baked goods\n2. Cheese\n3. Wine\n4. Dried meats\n5. Fruit drinks\n6. Yogurt\n7. Pickled foods\n8. Cosmetics and personal care products\n\nIt is considered safe by food regulatory agencies when used in recommended amounts and is largely non-toxic. Its primary function is to extend the shelf life of products by inhibiting microbial growth.",
